THIRD-PARTY LIBRARIES BUNDLED OR LINKED IN RELEASE BUILDS

The following third-party components are compiled into, dynamically
linked against, or bundled inside Release builds of WaveEdit. Each is
listed with its license, copyright, and upstream URL. Full license
texts are in the JUCE/ submodule and (where applicable) alongside the
bundled binary.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LAME MP3 Encoder
- Used for: MP3 export
- License: LGPL-2.1-or-later
- Copyright: © 1998-2017 The LAME Project
- Homepage: https://lame.sourceforge.io/
- How we ship it: dynamically linked. The macOS Release build bundles
  libmp3lame.dylib inside `WaveEdit.app/Contents/Frameworks/`; the
  Windows Release build bundles lame_enc.dll next to `WaveEdit.exe`;
  the Linux Release build bundles libmp3lame.so next to the executable.
- LGPL note: the LAME library is dynamically linked and bundled
  unmodified. Users who want to substitute a different LAME build can
  replace the bundled library file in place. LAME source can be
  obtained from the upstream URL above.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
